Subject: Bluetooth: HCI: Add IPC(11) bus type
Patch-mainline: v6.13-rc1
Git-commit: 96e7c4273560be4744ba8c444bc6969745315251
References: jsc#PED-12286

Zephyr(1) has been using the same bus defines as Linux so tools likes of
btmon, etc, are able to decode the bus used by the driver to transport
HCI packets.

Link: https://github.com/zephyrproject-rtos/zephyr/pull/80808
Signed-off-by: Luiz Augusto von Dentz <luiz.von.dentz@intel.com>
Acked-by: Chun-Yi Lee <jlee@suse.com>
---
 include/net/bluetooth/hci.h |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/include/net/bluetooth/hci.h
+++ b/include/net/bluetooth/hci.h
@@ -68,6 +68,7 @@
 #define HCI_I2C		8
 #define HCI_SMD		9
 #define HCI_VIRTIO	10
+#define HCI_IPC		11
 
 /* HCI device quirks */
